This paper deals with the specification of datatypes using term rewriting systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of rewrite rules to define arithmetic operations on natural numbers and integers, which could be considered a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) or data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of canonical term algebras, which is a concept in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the DDRSes and their ground-completeness, which could be considered a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
